olive oil
1 packet Baby Leaves
2 packet chicken breast
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tbs sesame oil
1 packet cornflour
2 tbs plain flour
1 packet Sichuan garlic paste
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
6 Mini Flour Tortillas

• Roughly chop baby leaves.
• In a large bowl, combine diced chicken, the soy sauce and sesame oil. Set aside.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to cover the base. Meanwhile, to the bowl with the chicken, add cornflour and the plain flour and toss to combine.
• When oil is hot, dust off any excess flour from chicken, then cook, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Drain excess oil from pan and add Sichuan garlic paste, tossing chicken, until coated.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine baby leaves, shredded cabbage mix, mayonnaise, a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts until warmed through.

• Bring everything to the table.
• Build your own tacos by topping with slaw and Sichuan glazed fried chicken. Enjoy!